<p data-start="9" data-end="59">You're talking about the little icon that appears:</p>
<ul data-start="60" data-end="122">
<li data-section-id="1k0ych7" data-start="60" data-end="80">
<p data-start="62" data-end="80">on the browser tab</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="1kpmio" data-start="81" data-end="95">
<p data-start="83" data-end="95">in bookmarks</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="1668vjl" data-start="96" data-end="122">
<p data-start="98" data-end="122">next to the website name</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="124" data-end="152">That's called a <strong data-start="140" data-end="151">favicon</strong>.</p>
<h3 data-section-id="1pv7xfb" data-start="154" data-end="178">How to add a favicon</h3>
<ol data-start="180" data-end="246">
<li data-section-id="n9fvre" data-start="180" data-end="203">
<p data-start="183" data-end="203">Use your logo image.</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="1lvn6aq" data-start="204" data-end="246">
<p data-start="207" data-end="246">Upload it to your GitHub repository as:</p>
</li>
</ol>
